      "intro": "If you're caring for a loved one 60+ with functional deficits or Alzheimer's in Pennsylvania, this program reimburses you for respite care, supplies, and other caregiving expenses. The reimbursement percentage depends on your loved one's household income, up to 100% for lower incomes, scaled down to 0% above 380% of the Federal Poverty Level ($58,320 for a single person in 2026).\n\nYou pay upfront for approved services and submit receipts for reimbursement. Beyond financial help, the program provides care management, caregiver education, and training at no cost regardless of income. An in-home assessment determines what services you're authorized to receive.\n\nThe program also covers caregivers 55+ raising grandchildren or caring for disabled adult children (18-59) with different co-residence requirements. Each of Pennsylvania's 52 counties administers the program through their Area Agency on Aging, so services and wait times may vary by location.",
